Do you think she
knows something?

22:03.458 --> 22:06.458
Julian thought maybe Lewis
was protecting someone else.

22:06.458 --> 22:08.417
Her? No way.

22:08.417 --> 22:09.792
She'd never cheat.

22:09.792 --> 22:11.375
I would have said
the same about Lewis.

22:12.834 --> 22:14.208
You're alright?

22:14.208 --> 22:17.083
- It was a paper on evolution.
- So?

22:17.083 --> 22:19.458
Two years ago, Savannah was
a homeschooled Evangelical

22:19.458 --> 22:21.834
who was probably taught
that evolution was a myth

22:21.834 --> 22:24.458
perpetuated by Satanists
who sucked the blood of

22:24.458 --> 22:26.125
un-baptized Christian babies.

22:26.125 --> 22:28.166
I don't think they teach it
quite that way.

22:28.166 --> 22:30.375
I said probably.

22:30.375 --> 22:32.000
The truth is, that Lewis
never would have made it

22:32.000 --> 22:35.333
'on the squad if Savannah
hadn't saved his ass.'

22:35.333 --> 22:37.834
He owed her...big time.

22:37.834 --> 22:39.583
Big enough to cheat?

22:43.500 --> 22:45.458
- Let's find out.
- Whoa, what are you doing?

22:45.458 --> 22:48.000
- Alice!
- Hey, Savannah.

22:48.000 --> 22:49.792
Are you a big disgusting
liar or what?

22:49.792 --> 22:52.333
- I'm sorry?
- Alice, whoa. This is way out--

22:52.333 --> 22:54.125
- What did you just say?
- Oh, hell. This is not--

22:54.125 --> 22:56.041
- No, really. You heard me.
- 'Alice.'

22:56.041 --> 22:57.417
Because if you're
actually letting Lewis

22:57.417 --> 22:59.208
take the fall for something
that you did...

22:59.208 --> 23:01.208
No, no, no. You are way out of
line right now. Alice!

23:01.208 --> 23:03.208
It's unworthy of you and
it's unworthy of the squad.

23:03.208 --> 23:04.542
Alice.

23:08.708 --> 23:10.667
Nothing to say?

23:15.208 --> 23:17.125
I guess that says it all.

23:18.542 --> 23:21.500
[Savannah sobbing]

23:24.583 --> 23:26.834
I'm sorry.

23:26.834 --> 23:28.959
I'm so sorry.

23:28.959 --> 23:31.500
I feel like the worst person
in the world.

23:33.542 --> 23:35.083
Hey.

23:35.083 --> 23:36.417
Breathe, breathe.
It's important to breathe.

23:36.417 --> 23:37.542
It's okay. It's okay.

23:37.542 --> 23:39.125
'It's okay.'

23:39.125 --> 23:40.583
'Breathe.
It's important to breathe.'

23:40.583 --> 23:41.959
- It's alright.
- We should...

23:43.375 --> 23:45.083
We should take this elsewhere.

23:45.083 --> 23:46.417
[crying]

23:46.417 --> 23:47.959
Come on.

23:51.250 --> 23:53.500
It was my first time
at a secular school.

23:54.917 --> 23:57.750
I was a nervous wreck.

23:57.750 --> 24:00.875
Everything was so strange
and alien

24:00.875 --> 24:05.083
and then I get to a class where
everyone understood evolution.

24:05.083 --> 24:06.750
'I had trouble wrapping
my head around'

24:06.750 --> 24:09.500
everyone assuming
it was just scientific fact.

24:11.750 --> 24:12.917
And then the Professor

24:12.917 --> 24:14.875
made fun of me
in front of everybody...

24:16.417 --> 24:19.083
And I don't know.

24:19.083 --> 24:22.041
Got stubborn, angry...

24:23.458 --> 24:25.959
I let myself get mental.

24:25.959 --> 24:28.125
'It was stupid.'

24:28.125 --> 24:30.250
Especially knowing
how high the stakes were.

24:31.417 --> 24:33.250
'So, there I was...'

24:33.250 --> 24:36.166
...refusing to write the paper
that was due the next morning.

24:37.792 --> 24:39.708
And then Lewis yelled at me.

24:39.708 --> 24:41.458
You yelled?

24:41.458 --> 24:42.458
Yeah, I was pissed.

24:42.458 --> 24:44.166
Come on, Savannah.

24:44.166 --> 24:45.875
She'd just given up
so much to come here

24:45.875 --> 24:47.625
and then
she just-just checked out.

24:47.625 --> 24:49.291
Wake up!

24:49.291 --> 24:51.250
I just reminded her that
flunking out of Lancer

24:51.250 --> 24:53.333
meant going back home with
her tail between her legs.

24:54.625 --> 24:57.959
You can't just
give up, Savannah.

24:57.959 --> 24:59.834
We need you.

24:59.834 --> 25:01.083
There's nothing I can do.

25:01.083 --> 25:02.333
Well, let me help you.

25:02.333 --> 25:03.500
I-I can help you.

25:03.500 --> 25:04.792
'I can.'

25:04.792 --> 25:06.375
How?

25:06.375 --> 25:09.000
So then Lewis offered
to help me write the paper.

25:09.000 --> 25:11.583
I didn't know
much about evolution so...

25:13.125 --> 25:15.959
That's where Betsy came in.

25:15.959 --> 25:18.000
You know what to do if
you get caught, right?

25:18.000 --> 25:19.458
Forget your name.

25:19.458 --> 25:21.375
Pleasure doing business
with you.

25:26.125 --> 25:28.834
(Lewis)
So, I bought a paper
from Betsy.

25:28.834 --> 25:31.834
My intention was to only
use it as a reference.

25:31.834 --> 25:33.250
(Savannah)
When I realized
what you'd done

25:33.250 --> 25:35.125
I didn't know what to think.

25:35.125 --> 25:36.500
We should have
burned the thing.

25:36.500 --> 25:39.083
We'll use that as a guideline.

25:39.083 --> 25:41.375
(Savannah)
But we agreed that we'd never
copy directly off the paper

25:41.375 --> 25:45.750
and...we convinced ourselves
it was okay.

25:45.750 --> 25:47.834
(Lewis)
'And it just, uh,
it was just getting'

25:47.834 --> 25:50.250
later and later
and...we were getting

25:50.250 --> 25:52.125
exhausted and...

25:52.125 --> 25:55.041
[keyboard clacking]

26:03.291 --> 26:06.208
[dramatic music]

26:17.208 --> 26:21.208
So I used it...or
a lot of it at least.

26:21.208 --> 26:23.375
Okay, I get all that,
but what don't understand

26:23.375 --> 26:25.375
is why Lewis is so dead set
on taking the fall alone.

26:25.375 --> 26:27.166
(Dan)
'Come on, M.'

26:27.166 --> 26:29.375
If he tells the honor court
he never turned in the paper

26:29.375 --> 26:32.333
they're gonna to ask the
same questions you guys did.

26:32.333 --> 26:33.875
They're gonna ask who did.

26:40.750 --> 26:42.583
I created the
opportunity, alright?

26:42.583 --> 26:44.375
It never even would have
occurred to Savannah to cheat

26:44.375 --> 26:46.583
if I hadn't bought that paper
and that's on me.

26:46.583 --> 26:49.750
Plus...when you're caught
cheating

26:49.750 --> 26:50.959
you either get suspended
or you get an "F"

26:50.959 --> 26:53.291
in the class, right?

26:53.291 --> 26:56.083
Well, if I'm suspended,
the Hellcats, they lose a base

26:56.083 --> 26:58.375
'a few weeks before Nationals
and that would be bad'

26:58.375 --> 27:00.917
'but it wouldn't be a disaster.'

27:00.917 --> 27:04.250
Now, if Savannah gets suspended,
we not only lose

27:04.250 --> 27:08.291
our-our best flyer,
we lose our captain.

27:08.291 --> 27:09.625
That will be a disaster.

27:09.625 --> 27:11.000
Best flyer?

27:14.000 --> 27:15.000
Hardly.

27:16.792 --> 27:21.166
Bottom-line, no one here is
going to rat you out, okay?

27:22.458 --> 27:24.834
I assume that's true, Alice?

27:26.792 --> 27:28.083
Mm-hmm.

27:28.083 --> 27:31.291
(Marti)
'So, the question is...'

27:31.291 --> 27:32.875
...what do you want to do next?

27:35.083 --> 27:38.000
[dramatic music]

27:42.000 --> 27:44.375
I'm gonna to do what I should
have done in the first place.

27:45.417 --> 27:46.750
I'm gonna come clean.

27:46.750 --> 27:49.125
Savannah, that's not
a good idea. The team...

27:49.125 --> 27:50.959
Has been through worse.

27:50.959 --> 27:53.458
Listen, I have to face
the mistakes I've made

27:53.458 --> 27:55.500
and live with the consequences.

27:55.500 --> 27:58.500
I can't just pretend like
the past is gonna to go away.

27:58.500 --> 28:00.458
'I can't live my life
that way.'

28:03.333 --> 28:06.291
Listen...

28:06.291 --> 28:09.125
...I know you think
you're responsible...

28:09.125 --> 28:10.417
...but it's not your fault.

28:12.125 --> 28:13.875
It was my name on the paper...

28:14.834 --> 28:16.750
My responsibility.

28:19.041 --> 28:20.834
Thank you.

28:24.708 --> 28:26.667
Marti, will you defend me?

28:28.667 --> 28:30.542
Of course.

28:30.542 --> 28:31.750
Thanks.

28:35.208 --> 28:38.125
I'm going to go e-mail the Dean,
tell him the truth.

28:42.250 --> 28:44.041
[door closes]

28:44.041 --> 28:46.041
[indistinct chatter]

28:46.041 --> 28:48.208
- 'Still got it, coach.'
- That was fierce.

28:48.208 --> 28:49.542
It was fun, right?

28:49.542 --> 28:51.500
Vanessa, we need to talk.

28:55.208 --> 28:57.542
- We have a problem.
- What's the problem?

28:57.542 --> 28:59.041
Um...

28:59.041 --> 29:00.375
[gasps]

29:00.375 --> 29:02.500
Man, I think,
Emily just walked in.

29:04.250 --> 29:05.875
Yeah, that'd be the problem.

29:05.875 --> 29:08.041
[sighs]

29:08.041 --> 29:12.291
So, you obviously knew Lewis was
taking the fall for Savannah.

29:12.291 --> 29:15.750
Look, after we heard her arguing
with Lewis, I asked her.

29:15.750 --> 29:17.583
She swore me to secrecy.

29:17.583 --> 29:19.125
I'm sorry, I couldn't tell you.

29:20.083 --> 29:21.959
I'm your best friend.

29:21.959 --> 29:23.667
And she's my girlfriend.

29:25.959 --> 29:28.125
Look, when I came back
from New Orleans

29:28.125 --> 29:31.583
we both agreed our relationship
had to be different.

29:31.583 --> 29:33.500
So we don't make
the same mistakes.

29:35.250 --> 29:37.625
So, now it's different.

29:44.583 --> 29:47.291
That-That's probably
a good thing, huh?

29:47.291 --> 29:49.834
(Dan)
'Yeah, I think so.'

29:49.834 --> 29:51.583
'Hey, you want anything snacky?'

29:53.250 --> 29:55.875
No. I'm...not hungry.

29:59.000 --> 30:00.959
They hired her?

30:00.959 --> 30:03.125
She was on the legal staff
for the NCAA

30:03.125 --> 30:04.625
but she left to freelance.

30:04.625 --> 30:05.834
There are no shortage of schools

30:05.834 --> 30:08.291
needing her kind
of inside information.

30:08.291 --> 30:10.291
But she works for us, right?

30:10.291 --> 30:11.625
On our side?

30:11.625 --> 30:13.000
She works for the school.

30:13.000 --> 30:14.959
And the school
is on the school's side.

30:14.959 --> 30:16.792
Well, we bent a lot of rules

30:16.792 --> 30:18.959
trying to get Travis
out of prison.

30:18.959 --> 30:20.667
We did more than bend rules.

30:20.667 --> 30:22.417
[exhales]
Well, it's in the past.

30:22.417 --> 30:25.625
I'm sure Emily's moved on
and we should do the same.

30:25.625 --> 30:28.417
Let's just go to her before she
comes to us because...

30:28.417 --> 30:29.542
Red?

30:30.458 --> 30:32.000
Emily, hi.

30:34.166 --> 30:35.625
Hey, Emily.

30:35.625 --> 30:37.959
And Vanessa the cheerleader.

30:37.959 --> 30:40.667
I hear you're coaching
the Hellcats now.

30:40.667 --> 30:42.333
Yes, I am.

30:42.333 --> 30:44.250
'Uh, we go to Nationals
in a couple of weeks.'

30:44.250 --> 30:45.667
Oh, that's fantastic.

30:45.667 --> 30:47.583
I always knew
you had a bright future.

30:50.834 --> 30:52.542
So, you two are together?

30:52.542 --> 30:53.625
- What? No.
- No, no.

30:53.625 --> 30:54.959
We're just friends.

30:54.959 --> 30:58.625
Oh, um, not according
to the report.

30:58.625 --> 31:00.291
Report?

31:00.291 --> 31:02.000
Uh, from the
private investigator.

31:02.000 --> 31:04.208
I've been having members of
the coaching staff followed.

31:04.208 --> 31:05.834
[scoffs]

31:05.834 --> 31:06.875
[chuckles]

31:06.875 --> 31:08.000
God.

31:08.000 --> 31:09.500
Look at the two of you.

31:09.500 --> 31:10.667
You're like
a couple of teenagers

31:10.667 --> 31:12.583
caught groping in the basement.

31:13.667 --> 31:15.500
I'm kidding.

31:15.500 --> 31:16.583
[chuckling]

31:16.583 --> 31:18.417
Oh.

31:18.417 --> 31:20.208
Probably.

31:22.875 --> 31:24.000
Guys, there's no reason
to be awkward.

31:24.000 --> 31:25.083
It was ten years ago.

31:25.083 --> 31:26.917
It's...water under the bridge.

31:26.917 --> 31:28.000
Whoosh.

31:28.000 --> 31:29.708
[laughing]

31:29.708 --> 31:33.834
Well, in that case,
yes, we are together.

31:38.542 --> 31:40.708
That's wonderful.

31:40.708 --> 31:43.250
I hope he makes you every bit
as happy as he made me.

31:48.875 --> 31:50.875
That woman wants us dead.

31:50.875 --> 31:52.792
You picked up
on that, did ya?

31:56.708 --> 31:59.875
Do you understand the charges
against you, Miss Monroe?

31:59.875 --> 32:01.125
Yes, Your Honor.

32:01.125 --> 32:02.917
And you understand
the range of punishments

32:02.917 --> 32:05.458
we will be deciding on
if you plead guilty?

32:05.458 --> 32:07.083
Yes, Your Honor.

32:07.083 --> 32:08.458
And how do you plead?

32:10.375 --> 32:12.375
Guilty.

32:12.375 --> 32:14.417
Would counsel like to say
anything before we decide

32:14.417 --> 32:16.917
which punishment
is more appropriate?

32:16.917 --> 32:19.041
Yes, Your Honors, I would.

32:19.041 --> 32:20.375
Miss Perkins?

32:27.458 --> 32:29.667
Positive outcomes only.

32:29.667 --> 32:32.708
That's Savannah Monroe's mantra.

32:32.708 --> 32:35.583
She sees the positive
in everything.

32:35.583 --> 32:37.333
In everyone.

32:37.333 --> 32:40.250
It starts off annoying but
quickly becomes contagious.

32:40.250 --> 32:42.625
You stand next to this woman,
you can't help being

32:42.625 --> 32:45.959
affected by her hope,
her optimism, her wild

32:45.959 --> 32:48.083
enthusiasm for what comes next.

32:50.125 --> 32:55.250
Doubt is...everywhere today.

32:55.250 --> 32:58.125
Doubt becomes cynicism,
which influences what we do

32:58.125 --> 33:00.959
how we feel about each other
and ourselves.

33:00.959 --> 33:04.083
It colors our interactions,
but not Savannah's.

33:06.500 --> 33:09.583
A few months ago
I lost my scholarship.

33:09.583 --> 33:12.125
I almost had to give up
my dream of being a lawyer.

33:13.250 --> 33:15.583
I was desperate.

33:15.583 --> 33:17.000
I lashed out.

33:17.000 --> 33:18.792
'I insulted her world view.'

33:18.792 --> 33:21.792
I ended up calling her names
like "football groupie"

33:21.792 --> 33:24.125
and "bobblehead."

33:24.125 --> 33:25.792
[chuckles]

33:25.792 --> 33:27.250
'I gave her good reason
to write me off'

33:27.250 --> 33:29.166
'but she didn't do that.'

33:29.166 --> 33:30.708
She forgave me.

33:32.333 --> 33:35.667
She embraced me as a friend
and as a teammate.

33:35.667 --> 33:38.000
And in the process...

33:40.959 --> 33:42.583
...she saved my life.

33:44.291 --> 33:47.000
'She saved my dream
of becoming a lawyer one day.'

33:47.000 --> 33:49.667
Well, God and
the Tennessee State Bar willing.

33:49.667 --> 33:50.834
[people laughing]

33:50.834 --> 33:52.333
[Marti sighs]

33:52.333 --> 33:54.250
I haven't always been
the best friend to her.

33:55.333 --> 33:58.667
'I've done things I regret.'

33:58.667 --> 34:02.792
'But Savannah believes that
every tomorrow is better'

34:02.792 --> 34:04.750
'than today and...'

34:06.208 --> 34:08.208
Every day we all become
a little better

34:08.208 --> 34:09.958
than the day before.

34:17.625 --> 34:21.750
Savannah inspires me to live up
to that expectation.

34:22.875 --> 34:26.667
'And I'm not the only one.'

34:26.667 --> 34:29.917
For a lot of people,
people in this room

34:29.917 --> 34:31.875
she is our compass.

34:34.125 --> 34:38.750
Your Honors...Savannah Monroe
deserves to be punished.

34:38.750 --> 34:40.708
On that we can all agree.

34:40.708 --> 34:43.708
'I'm simply asking that while
you're making your decision'

34:43.708 --> 34:45.917
'you see the world as she does.'

34:45.917 --> 34:48.250
Allow her to continue
at this university.

34:48.250 --> 34:50.208
Allow her to keep
making the world

34:50.208 --> 34:52.542
around her
incrementally better.

34:54.375 --> 34:58.125
Let positive outcomes only
guide your sentencing.

35:02.208 --> 35:03.542
Thank you.

35:06.750 --> 35:08.417
Thank you, Miss Perkins.

35:08.417 --> 35:10.333
You'll have our answer shortly.

35:14.667 --> 35:15.792
[door opens]

35:21.708 --> 35:24.417
Hey, aren't you lucky
you got off easy?

35:24.417 --> 35:26.083
Academic probation.

35:26.083 --> 35:27.708
If it were up to me right now,
I'd be the one standing

35:27.708 --> 35:29.125
up there, not Savannah.

35:29.125 --> 35:31.125
Oh, Lewis, when are
you going to stop

35:31.125 --> 35:33.458
being the martyr all the time?

35:33.458 --> 35:35.583
Martyrs aren't sexy.

35:35.583 --> 35:38.542
Unless you're Milla Jovovich
and Joan of Arc.

35:38.542 --> 35:41.458
Mm. I would not kick her
out of bed.

35:41.458 --> 35:43.125
[laughing]

35:43.125 --> 35:44.458
Yeah, I got better things
to do than to try

35:44.458 --> 35:45.667
to make you think I'm sexy.

35:45.667 --> 35:48.583
Well, you used to do it
without trying.

35:48.583 --> 35:51.500
- Occasionally still do.
- Only occasionally?

35:51.500 --> 35:54.041
[chuckles]
I learned my lesson.

35:54.041 --> 35:55.625
Hah, please.

35:55.625 --> 35:57.625
Ain't nobody teach you anything?

35:57.625 --> 35:59.291
Probably not.

35:59.291 --> 36:01.291
But isn't it fun to try?

36:01.291 --> 36:03.291
[laughs]

36:03.291 --> 36:05.041
Occasionally.

36:06.083 --> 36:08.250
[laughing]

36:08.250 --> 36:10.041
- Oh, you know, I was...
- I always wondered.

36:12.834 --> 36:14.625
Go ahead.

36:14.625 --> 36:15.917
No, you.

36:18.625 --> 36:20.834
[door opens]

36:20.834 --> 36:22.667
'The verdict's in.'

36:22.667 --> 36:24.041
That didn't take long.

36:24.041 --> 36:25.166
(Alice)
'Maybe that's a good sign?'

36:25.166 --> 36:26.875
(Lewis)
'Yeah, or bad.'

36:26.875 --> 36:28.458
I'm gonna to go get
Marti and Savannah.

36:41.458 --> 36:44.041
Thank you for your patience.

36:44.041 --> 36:47.000
(female judge#1)
'We have reached a consensus.'

36:47.000 --> 36:49.750
Miss Monroe violated what is
perhaps the most important

36:49.750 --> 36:53.000
part of the student honor code,
the trust that exists

36:53.000 --> 36:56.458
between an academic institution
and it's students.

36:56.458 --> 37:00.000
'Failure is a vital part
of our educational system.'

37:00.000 --> 37:03.500
It is why we must
punish Miss Monroe.

37:03.500 --> 37:07.375
However, our justice system
exists to reform.

37:07.375 --> 37:09.333
And given Miss Monroe's
significant contribution

37:09.333 --> 37:12.708
to the Lancer community,
as well as the circumstances

37:12.708 --> 37:16.041
'under which she violated
the student honor code...'

37:16.041 --> 37:17.667
...we have concluded that
she is to be given

37:17.667 --> 37:19.375
a failing grade in the class.

37:19.375 --> 37:20.542
[sighs]

37:20.542 --> 37:21.667
'Court adjourned.'

37:21.667 --> 37:23.041
[indistinct chatter]

37:23.041 --> 37:24.917
Right, we pulled it off.

37:24.917 --> 37:26.375
Alright.

37:26.375 --> 37:27.834
I've never been so happy
to fail in my life.

37:27.834 --> 37:30.208
- Thank you, Marti.
- You're welcome. Wow.

37:30.208 --> 37:32.166
I will see you all at Nationals.

37:32.166 --> 37:33.333
Copy that.

37:33.333 --> 37:35.417
Who's up for drinks? Huh?

37:35.417 --> 37:37.125
- Alice is buying.
- You wish.

37:37.125 --> 37:38.542
(Dan)
'An amazing job, M.'

37:38.542 --> 37:41.250
Next time I go on
a demented killing spree

37:41.250 --> 37:43.375
- I want you representing me.
- Yeah, you got it.

37:43.375 --> 37:44.417
I'm proud of you, kiddo.

37:44.417 --> 37:45.750
- Thanks.
- Good job.

37:49.291 --> 37:51.750
[Alice laughing]

37:51.750 --> 37:57.959
♪ When the rain is blowing
in your face ♪

37:57.959 --> 38:04.250
♪ And the whole world
is on your case ♪

38:04.250 --> 38:10.125
♪ I could offer you
a warm embrace ♪

38:10.125 --> 38:14.417
♪ To make you feel my love ♪

38:16.458 --> 38:18.375
♪ When the evening shadows ♪

38:18.375 --> 38:22.500
♪ And the stars appear ♪

38:22.500 --> 38:29.291
♪ And there is no one there
to dry your tears ♪

38:29.291 --> 38:33.834
♪ I could hold you
for a million years ♪

38:33.834 --> 38:35.125
Hey.

38:35.125 --> 38:38.458
♪ To make you
feel my love ♪

38:38.458 --> 38:41.417
How'd you do?

38:41.417 --> 38:44.542
Probation for Lewis and
Savannah avoided suspension.

38:45.667 --> 38:48.208
Well, I would call that a win.

38:48.208 --> 38:50.333
Shouldn't you be out
celebrating your victory?

38:50.333 --> 38:51.959
No, I wasn't into it.

38:51.959 --> 38:55.583
I...came here. I thought maybe
I could help with something?

38:55.583 --> 38:56.667
You know, keep busy.

38:56.667 --> 38:59.166
Uh, well, um...

38:59.166 --> 39:00.542
- I can check.
- No, no, no, no.

39:00.542 --> 39:02.333
Uh, I don't want to keep you.

39:03.667 --> 39:05.583
I'll just head on then.

39:07.834 --> 39:09.000
Alright.

39:12.000 --> 39:16.750
♪ No doubt in my mind
where you belong ♪

39:18.834 --> 39:22.291
Thank you...Julian.

39:22.291 --> 39:24.000
Thank me?

39:24.000 --> 39:25.333
For what?

39:28.458 --> 39:31.458
For your...belief in me.

39:33.333 --> 39:35.458
For always encouraging me to...

39:36.959 --> 39:38.917
...go after what I want.

39:41.208 --> 39:44.583
Helping Travis and Lewis

39:44.583 --> 39:48.500
even when you think
it's-it's a mistake.

39:48.500 --> 39:51.041
I just wanted to see what you
were going to pull off next.

40:07.500 --> 40:13.583
♪ The storms are raging
on the rolling sea ♪

40:13.583 --> 40:19.667
♪ And on the highway
of regret ♪

40:19.667 --> 40:25.708
♪ Though winds of change
are blowing wild and free ♪

40:25.708 --> 40:31.708
♪ You ain't seen
nothing like me yet ♪

40:31.708 --> 40:36.792
♪ I could make you happy
make your dreams come true ♪

40:40.417 --> 40:44.208
I should go, huh?

40:44.208 --> 40:47.750
Yeah, I think that would
probably be the wise decision.

40:50.708 --> 40:53.750
♪ To make you feel my love ♪

40:53.750 --> 40:55.500
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight...

40:56.583 --> 40:57.959
...Miss Perkins.

40:57.959 --> 41:01.583
♪ Make you feel my love ♪

41:03.959 --> 41:08.333
♪ To make you feel my love ♪♪

41:11.417 --> 41:12.959
♪ One two three four ♪

41:12.959 --> 41:15.041
♪ Move to the left
move to the right ♪

41:15.041 --> 41:17.542
♪ If you stand still
you'll be here all night ♪

41:17.542 --> 41:20.125
♪ Ah aa ah aa ♪

41:20.125 --> 41:22.125
♪ Ah aa ah aa ♪

41:22.125 --> 41:24.667
♪ Move to the left
move to the right ♪

41:24.667 --> 41:27.166
♪ If you stand still
you'll be here all night ♪

41:27.166 --> 41:30.583
♪ Ah aa ah aa ♪
♪ Doesn't mean you belong ♪♪
